      },
      "date": "2017-07-05 09:55:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(4 comments)\n\n> Also, it looks like it will record _every_ open, instead of\n > limiting this to the first opener per file or similar?\n\nFollowing your suggestion in LU-9727, I plan to limit open records based on UID/GID, so that a file opened by the the same user from multiple nodes simultaneously only generates one open record. It will be the purpose of a subsequent patch, once UID/GID information is available in changelog entries.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
