    },
    {
      "id": "cb76c0e06e645c2b80e22f0ea8bc4597c527d0ba",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 729,
        "name": "Matthew S",
        "email": "matthew.sanderson.au@gmail.com",
        "username": "mattsanu"
      },
      "date": "2017-07-06 02:33:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> (4 comments)\n > \n > > Also, it looks like it will record _every_ open, instead of\n > > limiting this to the first opener per file or similar?\n > \n > Following your suggestion in LU-9727, I plan to limit open records\n > based on UID/GID, so that a file opened by the the same user from\n > multiple nodes simultaneously only generates one open record. It\n > will be the purpose of a subsequent patch, once UID/GID information\n > is available in changelog entries.\n\nIn theory, could multiple opens of a single file by a single user in a single HPC job, which should get merged into only a single OPEN record, get interleaved in time with other unrelated filesystem activity? That could make it more difficult to merge such multiple file opens into a single OPEN record.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
